This solution uses a simple approach to check if the string can become a palindrome after deleting at most one character. It iterates from both ends of the string and compares characters until they meet in the middle. If at any point the characters don't match, the function returns false, indicating that the string cannot become a palindrome. If the iteration completes without finding a mismatch, the function returns true, indicating that the string can become a palindrome after deleting at most one character. The time complexity is O(n) because the algorithm checks each character exactly once, and the space complexity is O(1) as it uses a constant amount of space.

